      "writtenOn": "2018-05-07T13:21:11Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Creating a release just adds a new image version to the docker container repository, but running pushk modifies the .yaml files, so if you want to push more than one application, for example, both iap_proxy and configmap-reload, then one of them will get marked as \u0027dirty\u0027 since a file has changed.\n\nThe solution is to break it into two steps: build releases, then \u0027pushk\u0027 so that all the .yaml updates are done at once.",
      "parentUuid": "a8e59eee_0d97b8cb",
      "revId": "c3584769f528f4f54af5158e190562014f06275f",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02",
      "unresolved": true
    },
